{
  "stem": "19210.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 201.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's how come I joined the British Army as a Bulgarian, native of Sofia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because I knew one thing, that the British, they don't speak Bulgarian anymore I didn't, right?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So in my British Army papers, I am a Bulgarian.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we went to-- we were taken from Sarafand to Ismailia in Egypt.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can't remember names of officers or anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I just get-- we had British drill sergeants, Irish drill sergeants, Scottish, Israelis.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we spent some time in the ITD, the so-called Infantry Training Depot.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had accelerated training.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All the Jewish Brigade was trained very acceleratedly so we could be going to war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But basically, the end of the war came at that point in time when we were in training in Egypt.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So ultimately, we went to-- we ended up in Europe with BAOR, the so-called British Army On the Rhine, was the abbreviation of it, but with the Jewish Brigade.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was then switched to the corps of military police.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I served with the 79th Unit of the British Military Police, within the Jewish Brigade Group.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And if I may say, one of the most touchy experiences that I ever had with refugees of the Holocaust was with the dispersed persons.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because I was on duty with another fellow next to the main train station in Antwerpen, and that main train station, the central, was bringing the trains from Germany directly to Antwerpen.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the way, in Brussels was the center of the black market in Europe at that point in time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we always used to watch who was doing what, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But nevertheless, I was standing there, you know, at attention pretty much, like the military police stay, you know?",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
